Free Opera in the Park featuring Houston Grand Opera's Carmen, June 8-10!
Houston Grand Opera's sensational Multimedia Modular Stage production retur=
ns=20
for three FREE performances at Houston's Miller Outdoor Theatre on June 8-1=
0=20
at 8:30 p.m. Bizet's fiery gypsy Carmen, everybody's favorite femme fatale,=
=20
ignites the summer in a powerhouse production that had audiences and critic=
s=20
cheering when it was first unveiled in 1998.

Houston Grand Opera's revolutionary Multimedia Modular Stage (MMS), with it=
s=20
giant "live" video screens, hydraulic platforms, and hundreds of rotating,=
=20
colored lights takes the incredible energy onstage and transports it to the=
=20
farthest reaches of the outdoor venue with a visceral impact equal to that =
of=20
a rock concert!

Tickets for the reserved seating will be issued between the hours of 11:30a=
m=20
and 1:00pm through the Miller Theatre box office on the day of the=20
performance.  Any remaining tickets will be issued one hour before the=20
performance.

For additional information, visit HGO's web site at=20
www.houstongrandopera.org. Also see volunteer opportunities below.

